Ecogen's Stock Placement
Separately, Ecogen said it signed a letter of intent with
Chancellor Inc., a New York investment management firm. The
agreement is for a negotiated investment on behalf of a
Chancellor client of $5 million for 500,000 shares of newly
created convertible preferred stock and warrants to purchase
as much as 500,000 common shares at $14 a share.
   Ecogen shares dropped 62.5 cents to $13.125 in national
over-the-counter trading yesterday.